OL,3,CSupreme court rejects Trump's bid to
OL,4,Cappeal E. Jean Carroll sex abuse case
OL,6,FThe Supreme Court on Monday rejected a
OL,7,Fpush by US President Donald Trump to
OL,8,Fthrow out a jury's $5 million finding
OL,9,Fthat he sexually abused the writer E.
OL,10,FJean Carroll at a New York City
OL,11,Fdepartment store in the mid-1990s and
OL,12,Flater defamed her.
OL,14,FThe high court declined to take up the
OL,15,Fcase in a brief, unexplained order, as
OL,16,Fis typical. There were no noted
OL,17,Fdissents. Trump also plans to appeal
OL,18,Fanother $83.3 million verdict awarded
OL,19,Fto Carroll by a different jury after a
OL,20,Fsecond defamation trial, his lawyers
OL,21,Fhave said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
